InTheRingBehindBars:ThaiPrisonFights.name: In the Ring Behind Bars: Thai Prison Fights
InTheRingBehindBars:ThaiPrisonFights.summary: Would you fight a civilian for a shorter prison sentence? In this high-security prison in Bangkok, just that happens as inmates box outsiders for money, shorter sentences, and the greater glory of Thailand, showcasing their Muay Thai skills.

LasVegasMartialArtsTeacherShowingStudent.name: Las Vegas martial arts teacher showing students how Muay Thai transforms body, mind
LasVegasMartialArtsTeacherShowingStudent.summary: At Nak Muay Thai Lao, owner and Master Airr Phanthip is teaching his students that Muay Thai is more than fighting, but also a journey of self-improvement through the mind, body and soul.

MétisMuayThaiFighterFromWinnipegHopesToC.name: Métis Muay Thai fighter from Winnipeg hopes to compete in Thailand | APTN News
MétisMuayThaiFighterFromWinnipegHopesToC.summary: Ashley Viner is a Métis Muay Thai fighter from Winnipeg winning medals left and right. She has now set her eyes on making Team Canada to compete in the World Boxing Council’s upcoming international competition in Bangkok, Thailand.

MuayThaiChampion'Grandma'ShowsAgeIsOnlyA.name: Muay Thai Champion 'Grandma' Shows Age Is Only a Number | TaiwanPlus News
MuayThaiChampion'Grandma'ShowsAgeIsOnlyA.summary: In her sixties and winning gold medals, Chang Hui-chu is changing what it means to practice muay Thai.
